[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about a potential issue with creating an UpToDate target before copying, especially regarding timestamps. If I use Files.copy, it doesn’t preserve attributes by default, which means the target’s modification time might end up being in the future. I wonder if I need to check the target names relative to the destination and source class using SourceFileScanner. Does it call the mapper when checking for target existence? Let’s inspect that further to see if it’s actually necessary.
